Drain the @black beans{1%box}, but reserve the liquid. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%clove}. Peel then mince or grate the @ginger{1%thumb}. Thinly slice the @scallions{2}, keeping the whites and green separate. Quarter the @button mushrooms{4%ounce}. Drain the @water chestnuts{1%can}.

== Black Bean Sauce ==

Make the black bean sauce: heat @olive oil{1%tsp} in a medium #pot over medium
heat. Add the garlic, ginger, and half the @Chinese 5 spice{1%tbsp}. Cook
~{1%minute}, stirring frequently. Add the reserved black bean liquid and half
the black beans. Add the @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, @veggie stock concentrate{1},
and @water{1%cup} to the #pot. Bring to boil, then reduce to a simmer, for
~{15-20%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

== Chicken ==

Thinly slice the @chicken breasts{12%ounce}. Season the chicken with @salt{},
@pepper{}, and the remaining Chinese five-spice. Heat @olive oil{1%tsp} in a
large #pan over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the pan and cook, tossing,
for ~{5%minutes}, until cooked through. Set aside.

== Finishing ==

Add the @white wine vinegar{2%tablespoon} to the same pan over medium-high
heat. Deglaze the pan by scraping up the brown bits on the bottom of the pan.
Reduce liquid by half and add it to the #pot with the black bean mixture.

Heat another @olive oil{1%tsp} in the same pan over medium-high heat. Add the
mushrooms and scallion whites and cook, tossing, ~{5-6%minutes}, until golden
brown. Add the water chestnuts to the #pan. Cook, tossing, for an additional
~{2%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the remaining black beans, black bean sauce, and chicken to the #pan.
Stir to combine and heat through. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Serve divided between #bowls and garnished with scallion greens. Enjoy!

> Chinese five-spice is a pungent mix of star anise, cloves, cinnamon, Sichuan
> peppercorns, and fennel. Anise-forward and slightly sweet, it perfumes the
> dish with its unique aroma. Black bean sauce is a staple of Chinese cooking;
> our version utilizes black beans rather than fermented soy beans to bring a
> variety of textures to the dish.